<blockquote>
<p dir="auto">In this example i'm getting the latest <a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=laravel.vscode-laravel" rel="nofollow">https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=laravel.vscode-laravel</a> so the <code class="notranslate">id</code> is just the <code class="notranslate">itemName</code> just change the name for the extension you need:</p>
<h3 dir="auto">run it on pwsh</h3>
<div class="highlight highlight-source-powershell" dir="auto"><pre class="notranslate"><span class="pl-smi">$extensionId</span> <span class="pl-k">=</span> <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span>laravel.vscode-laravel<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span>
<span class="pl-smi">$publisher</span><span class="pl-k">,</span> <span class="pl-smi">$name</span> <span class="pl-k">=</span> <span class="pl-smi">$extensionId</span> <span class="pl-k">-split</span> <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">'</span>\.<span class="pl-pds">'</span></span>
<span class="pl-smi">$downloadUrl</span> <span class="pl-k">=</span> <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span>https://<span class="pl-smi">$publisher</span>.gallery.vsassets.io/_apis/public/gallery/publisher/<span class="pl-smi">$publisher</span>/extension/<span class="pl-smi">$name</span>/latest/assetbyname/Microsoft.VisualStudio.Services.VSIXPackage<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span>
<span class="pl-c1">Invoke-WebRequest</span> <span class="pl-k">-</span>Uri <span class="pl-smi">$downloadUrl</span> <span class="pl-k">-</span>OutFile <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$name</span>.vsix<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> <span class="pl-k">-</span>UseBasicParsing</pre></div>
</blockquote>
<p dir="auto">Thanks for great simple solution.</p>
<div class="highlight highlight-source-shell" dir="auto"><pre class="notranslate"><span class="pl-c"><span class="pl-c">#!</span>/bin/sh</span>

extensionId=<span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span>laravel.vscode-laravel<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span>
publisher=<span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">$(</span>echo <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$extensionId</span><span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> <span class="pl-k">|</span> cut -d <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">'</span>.<span class="pl-pds">'</span></span> -f 1<span class="pl-pds">)</span></span>
name=<span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">$(</span>echo <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$extensionId</span><span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> <span class="pl-k">|</span> cut -d <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">'</span>.<span class="pl-pds">'</span></span> -f 2<span class="pl-pds">)</span></span>
downloadUrl=<span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span>https://<span class="pl-smi">$publisher</span>.gallery.vsassets.io/_apis/public/gallery/publisher/<span class="pl-smi">$publisher</span>/extension/<span class="pl-smi">$name</span>/latest/assetbyname/Microsoft.VisualStudio.Services.VSIXPackage<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span>
curl -L <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$downloadUrl</span><span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> -o <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$name</span>.vsix<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span>
version=<span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">$(</span>unzip -p <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$name</span>.vsix<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> extension.vsixmanifest <span class="pl-k">|</span> grep -oP <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">'</span>&lt;Identity[^&gt;]+Version="\K[^"]+<span class="pl-pds">'</span></span><span class="pl-pds">)</span></span>
mv <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$name</span>.vsix<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">${extensionId}</span>-<span class="pl-smi">${version}</span>.vsix<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span></pre></div>
</blockquote>
<p dir="auto">I tweaked this a little so that it accepts the extension ID as a param, and added some validation / error handling</p>
<p dir="auto">(I'm on macOS, so I had to install GNU grep via <code class="notranslate">brew install grep</code> and then changed <code class="notranslate">grep</code> to <code class="notranslate">ggrep</code>. If you're on Linux you can probably change <code class="notranslate">ggrep</code> back to just <code class="notranslate">grep</code>)</p>
<div class="highlight highlight-source-shell" dir="auto"><pre class="notranslate"><span class="pl-c"><span class="pl-c">#!</span>/usr/bin/env bash</span>

<span class="pl-k">if</span> [ <span class="pl-smi">$#</span> <span class="pl-k">-lt</span> 1 ]<span class="pl-k">;</span> <span class="pl-k">then</span>
  <span class="pl-c1">echo</span> <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span>Usage: <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">$(</span>basename <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$0</span><span class="pl-pds">"</span></span><span class="pl-pds">)</span></span> &lt;extensionId&gt;<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span>
  <span class="pl-c1">exit</span> 1
<span class="pl-k">fi</span>

extensionId=<span class="pl-smi">$1</span>

<span class="pl-k">if</span> [[ <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$extensionId</span><span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> <span class="pl-k">!=</span> <span class="pl-k">*</span>.<span class="pl-k">*</span> ]]<span class="pl-k">;</span> <span class="pl-k">then</span>
  <span class="pl-c1">echo</span> <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span>Error: Extension ID must be of the form &lt;publisher&gt;.&lt;name&gt;<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span>
  <span class="pl-c1">exit</span> 1
<span class="pl-k">fi</span>

publisher=<span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">$(</span>echo <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$extensionId</span><span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> <span class="pl-k">|</span> cut -d <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">'</span>.<span class="pl-pds">'</span></span> -f 1<span class="pl-pds">)</span></span>
name=<span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">$(</span>echo <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$extensionId</span><span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> <span class="pl-k">|</span> cut -d <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">'</span>.<span class="pl-pds">'</span></span> -f 2<span class="pl-pds">)</span></span>

downloadUrl=<span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span>https://<span class="pl-smi">$publisher</span>.gallery.vsassets.io/_apis/public/gallery/publisher/<span class="pl-smi">$publisher</span>/extension/<span class="pl-smi">$name</span>/latest/assetbyname/Microsoft.VisualStudio.Services.VSIXPackage<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span>
curl -fL <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$downloadUrl</span><span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> -o <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$name</span>.vsix<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> <span class="pl-k">||</span> { <span class="pl-c1">echo</span> <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span>Error: Failed to download VSIX file<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span><span class="pl-k">;</span> <span class="pl-c1">exit</span> 1<span class="pl-k">;</span> }

version=<span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">$(</span>unzip -p <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$name</span>.vsix<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> extension.vsixmanifest <span class="pl-k">|</span> ggrep -oP <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">'</span>&lt;Identity[^&gt;]+Version="\K[^"]+<span class="pl-pds">'</span></span><span class="pl-pds">)</span></span>
mv <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$name</span>.vsix<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span> <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span><span class="pl-smi">$extensionId</span>-<span class="pl-smi">$version</span>.vsix<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span>

<span class="pl-c1">echo</span> <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">"</span>Downloaded <span class="pl-smi">$extensionId</span> version <span class="pl-smi">$version</span> to <span class="pl-smi">$extensionId</span>-<span class="pl-smi">$version</span>.vsix<span class="pl-pds">"</span></span></pre></div>
